      <hedline>
        <hl1>Same Tragic Mistake</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mary C Fisher letter says Bush administration ought to be preparing for worst-case, not best-case, scenario on global warming</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''White House Attacked for Letting States Lead on Climate'' (news article, Dec. 11), you refer to what many see as ''inaction'' on the president's part with regard to global climate change.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''White House Attacked for Letting States Lead on Climate'' (news article, Dec. 11), you refer to what many see as ''inaction'' on the president's part with regard to global climate change.</p>
        <p>The Bush administration, in forming its environmental policy, is making the same tragic mistake it made in Iraq. It is planning for the best-case scenario. A wise leader prepares for the worst-case scenario.</p>
        <p>MARY C. FISHER  Westerville, Ohio, Dec. 11, 2003</p>
      </block>
